description.plain:
Trap/hip hop/r&b star Deja Trimble (born April 8, 1991), got the nickname “Loaf” in high school due to her propensity to wear loafers. The rapper/singer/songwriter is now known by her stage name, Dej Loaf (stylized as DeJ Loaf).

Tragedy struck the Detroit, Michigan native  early: her father was killed when she was just 4 years old. As she grew up, Dej escaped from her troubles and her shyness by writing in her diary.  Dej studied nursing in college for three semesters but quit to pursue a music career, supporting herself by working as a janitor.

She released her first mixtape in 2012 and rose to fame in 2014 when her single “Try Me”, went viral after rap superstar Drake gave the song a shoutout. She has since appeared on other chart-hitting songs, such as “Detroit Vs. Everybody” and “Be Real.” She was also named one of XXL’s 2015 Freshmen.

songs.title: Try Me

description.plain:
“Try Me” is the breakout single from the diminutive Detroit sensation. Featuring chilled out production and a steady delivery from DeJ, the single got a huge bump when Drake quoted the “you should see my closet” line in an instagram post.

Peaking at #45 on the Billboard Top 100, the success of the single led to her signing with Columbia, working with Eminem, and touring with Nicki Minaj.
